Czech Ruling Party Eyes More Talks on Pension Revamp, Pravo Says

-- B y   P e t e r   L a c a
-- 
2011-03-09T07:05:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-09/czech-ruling-party-eyes-more-talks-on-pension-revamp-pravo-says.html
Lawmakers for the smallest Czech
ruling-coalition party, the Public Affairs, want more
negotiations on the planned overhaul of the pension system,
 Pravo  reported, citing a Public Affairs deputy Josef Novotny.  Leaders of the three Cabinet parties have agreed on a
pension revamp that will strengthen private saving for
retirement. Some Public Affairs deputies want the government to
raise taxes on gambling to secure more funding for the pension
overhaul, the newspaper reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Peter Laca in Prague at 
 placa@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Willy Morris at 
 wmorris@bloomberg.net  